If you have an indented line without a curly brace, the auto-indentation will try to keep lining things up to this instead of to the current indentation level.  Examples will be helpful:

If we have the following structure:

$return_val = SomeFunction($a, $b, $c,
    $d_on_newline_tabbed_in, $e, $f);

If I start typing on the line *after* the blank line, the editor will try tabbing me in; For example:

$return_val = SomeFunction($a, $b, $c,
    $d_on_newline_tabbed_in, $e, $f);

$start_typing_here

Would actually render:
$return_val = SomeFunction($a, $b, $c,
    $d_on_newline_tabbed_in, $e, $f);

    $start_typing_here

This pops up in several different cases:
if (empty($foo)
    || empty($bar))

When we hit 'enter' after the empty($bar)) line, it lines up with the "||" - which is fine.  But typing the curly braces breaks - it should be (autocompleted):

if (empty($foo)
    || empty($bar))
{
    $start_typing_here
}

but renders as:

if (empty($foo)
    || empty($bar))
    {
        $start_typing_here
    }

